            {
              "content": "=### ROLE\nYou are a strict data validation expert.\n\n### INPUT DATA\n1. Requested Fields: {{ $(\"Webhook\").item.json.body.parameters.fields }}\n2. Extracted Data (JSON Array): {{ JSON.stringify($json.extracted_data, null, 2) }}\n\n### VALIDATION RULES\n\n1. STRUCTURE CHECK\n- Data must be a non-empty ARRAY of objects\n\n2. FIELD COMPLETENESS\n- EACH object must contain ALL requested fields\n- Values must not be null, empty, or placeholders\n\n3. DATA SUFFICIENCY (VERY IMPORTANT)\n- The dataset must contain MULTIPLE items (not just 1 or 2)\n- Minimum acceptable items: 5 (or more depending on context)\n- Data should not be shallow (e.g., just title + 1 short line)\n\n4. QUALITY CHECK\n- Data should represent meaningful, usable content\n- Not partial previews or incomplete snippets\n\n### DECISION RULES\nReturn homepage_sufficient = true ONLY IF:\n- At least 5+ valid objects exist\n- AND each object contains all requested fields\n- AND data appears complete (not shallow or preview-like)\n\nOtherwise return false\n\n### OUTPUT\nReturn ONLY valid JSON:\n\n{\n  \"homepage_sufficient\": true/false,\n  \"reasoning\": \"...\",\n  \"missing_or_incomplete_fields\": []\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
